<p>I have just started learning Erlang but I can't figure out why this code doesn't match the function call test:sum(3)</p>  <pre><code>-module(test). -export([sum/1]).  sum(0) -&gt; 0; sum(N) when is_integer(N) and N&gt;0 -&gt; N + sum(N - 1). </code></pre>  <p>... while this does:</p>  <pre><code>-module(test). -export([sum/1]).  sum(0) -&gt; 0; sum(N) when is_integer(N), N&gt;0 -&gt; N + sum(N - 1). </code></pre>  <p>Am I missing something about the two different approaches?</p>